// Accept fixture: recursive lambda actor (self-reference via let-binding).
//
// The forward-bound let name is a WEAK capture (§5.9 ratification 2):
// the spawn boxes a capture env whose self field is back-filled with the
// DOWNGRADED handle after construction, and the body's recursive send
// dispatches through `hew_lambda_actor_weak_send` — upgraded just long
// enough to deliver, so the body never keeps its own actor alive past
// external refcount zero. The countdown self-sends 10 → 1 and prints
// once at the base case, proving every recursive hop delivered.
fn main() {
    let count = actor |n: i64| {
        if n == 1 {
            println("liftoff");
        }
        if n > 1 {
            count(n - 1);
        }
    };
    count(10);
    sleep_ms(400);
}
